In Greece, wine is deeply woven into the fabric of everyday society and is a central component of cultural history.&nbsp;
The country is one of the world&rsquo;s most ancient viticultural locations. References to consumption and cultivation appear in literature and historical texts as early as the 17th century B.C. Indigenous wine varieties once favored by Hesiod and Aristotle are still produced today.&nbsp;
