Losing a vineyard to disease is &ldquo;extremely painful,&rdquo; says Adam Tolmach, cofounder of The Ojai Vineyard. In 1981, he planted more than five acres of mostly Syrah on Ventura County land that his grandfather purchased a half-century earlier. His last vintage was in 1995.
&ldquo;You put your heart and soul into it,&rdquo; says Tolmach. &ldquo;I planted every one of the vines and nurtured them. It was like my baby that I was working on. It was very heartbreaking to have it slowly die off.&rdquo;
